reviews_data.review_text: PSL (hot) was a little off, bland or odd kind of taste. Pumpkin cold brew was very good!

Cutest little coffee shop in charming downtown! Pastries are locally made and always fresh, I recommend the blueberry muffins when they’re available. If you like coffee, my pick is the cookie butter iced latte!  You won’t be disappointed. Baristas are always friendly and the service is quick and consistent!

The shop itself is very cute and staff was friendly. The Iced chai latte was awful - the boxed chai they use was way too sugary and bland.; I wound up throwing it away.  I asked for almond milk and they almost used whole milk - but we caught it before they made it.  Overall as a Chai drinker - not the place for me.  Paris Baguette in Waverly has the BEST chai latte.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi there,
Thanks for visiting and for your honest feedback. I’m glad you enjoyed the space and our team, but I’m sorry the chai latte missed the mark. We’ve been using it for 3.5 years and our customers have loved it. We’ll definitely look into the sweetness and double-check our milk protocols to avoid mix-ups. Appreciate you giving us a try and we’re always working to improve! Please email me at dailygcoffee@gmail.com and I will be happy to give you a full refund! 
Best,
Mariya 
Owner, Daily Grind Coffee Bar

reviews_data.review_text: A fantastic addition to the neighborhood. The staff is awesome under a lot pressure being the new thing on the block. The wait is worth it. The coffee and fresh food is divine. We also appreciate the weekends and later hours where most others are closed.
Literally the best Café Waxhaw has! Definitely worth a visit!
Beautiful little space and a much needed spot to hang out in waxhaw. Glad to have a unique brand branch out into the area.

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Outdoor patio / terrace, Counter seating
review_questions.Parking options: Free parking lot, Free street parking

reviews_data.review_text:
DE. FRICKIN. LICIOUS.

If you call yourself a coffee fan, you need to be here. Enough said.
A great place!!!

Came here for the first time today, will be coming back. It is definitely my coffee shop. I’ve been stuck with starbucks for too long and I don’t think i’m ever gonna get starbucks again now that I have had this place. Everything was good, food and drinks. Lots of different flavor options and it’s just all so perfect. Service was quick, inside is small but so cute and has great vibes, and the outside area is adorable.
Very good variety of deserts! The coffee is among some of the best I have had! Both employees are kind as can be and very funny I would recommend anyone go give them a visit!

Very good and clean coffee shop in Waxhaw right by the public parking. I got a Shaken espresso brown sugar. Light oatmilk 2 extra shots of espresso with pumpkin spice foam, (give it a go its epic ) and a pastry. Pastry is the cake ish coffee bean shaped item definitely give those a go. I think this is the best coffee joint in waxhaw honestly. Everyone works hard, looks good, clean, put together and work as a unit as well.

Give this place a visit. Been 2x in 2 days and the coffee slapped each time.

I loved my experience here. Such a cute coffee shop w/ great merch & gift items. I ordered the butterfly matcha, & I think it’s the most beautiful drink I’ve ever ordered. I want to come back to try their iced matcha latte. Really cute spot.

Really sweet baristas working there. The best coffee I’ve had in a very long time and muffin. I got the s’mores latte and they torched the marshmallows. My sister tried the butterfly blue matcha and loved it. Also got a mango smoothie for my little one. They have the viral fruit pastries the coconut is 10/10. Cent wait to try the rest. Will definitely be back! Very cute space, straight out of a Pinterest board
Every single chair is tortuously uncomfortable. Had to leave. No sitting and chatting here. Also inside is so loud can’t hear conversation.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Christina, 

I’m sorry you felt this way about our atmosphere. With our shop being on the smaller side, it gets pretty loud inside. We do have couches outside with cushions but on a busy morning, they get reserved quickly. Aside from comfort, we hope you were able to enjoy our offerings! Have a great day. 

-Mariya

reviews_data.review_text: Went here for the first time this morning. Ordered an iced vanilla latte and coffee cake donut! Both were delicious and service was friendly and fast. Although it is tight inside there is plenty of seating outside as well. Would highly recommend!
Seriously such wonderful and nice people, quick service, only waited for maybe 5 minutes with a line out the door, and coffee was delish 🥰 Will definitely be back to try some delish looking desserts!
Great place to get daily coffee or catch up with friends! Love the location and choices they offer.
Waited for a good while, for two lattes!  Drinks were great but, place seemed short staffed

Great new coffee spot! Only suggestion is the hot coffee isn’t really hot, we asked for extra hot and still wasn’t very hot.
Very good pastries and donuts.
Yummy coffee, good service and cute space! Not a lot of room inside but decent seating. Love that they have a wide variety of flavor options

By far the best coffee I’ve had. Stumbled upon this place and wanted to see what the hype was about with the line out the door. I got a black drip coffee with a double shot and it was rich, notes of sweetness and not bitter like a lot of the places I’ve tried in Charlotte. I paired it with a muffin 20/10. Easily became a regular here within one visit.
Great coffee and delicious donuts! The service was fast and friendly.

reviews_data.review_text: Great place to hang out and have a great coffee

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Bar area, Outdoor patio / terrace, Counter seating

reviews_data.review_text: This is what Waxhaw was missing all these years!! I highly recommend you come see Daily Grind coffee for yourself! It’s such a cute coffee shop! The coffee and matcha was delicious! Outdoor seating is so cute too! They had the line moving really fast and efficient. We will definitely be back!

Supposed to have 3 shots of espresso in my wife’s iced coffee but it tasted like milk and they were out of black coffee, brewed more and somehow it was luke warm. DONT WASTE YOUR MONEY. Also wayyy to high of prices
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Logan, 
I’ve checked our records and we don’t have any receipts under your name, nor have we had any orders for a coffee with three shots since we opened.
Could you please email me at dailygrindwaxhaw@gmail.com so we can clarify this? I want to make sure you’ve reviewed the correct location, as I currently have no record of your visit.
Best regards,
Mariya

reviews_data.review_text: We continued our exploration of local coffee shops across the Charlotte area and ended up in Waxhaw at this brand new coffee shop.  The shop is really nice inside and there is nice outdoor seating as well.  There was plenty of parking nearby.  They had a bunch of pastries in addition to coffee or tea as well as a bunch of branded merch for sale.  Locally roasted beans are used for their coffee which is great because it supports other local businesses in the Charlotte area.  The drip coffee was good as well as the Latte we ordered.  Great place to hangout and is dog friendly!

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Outdoor patio / terrace

reviews_data.review_text: Daily Grind Coffee & Bar quickly became one of my favorite spots. The coffee was fantastic—smooth, rich, and made with care. The desserts were absolutely amazing too, the perfect pairing with my drink. Such a cozy and welcoming place, I’ll definitely be back!
Best coffee place in town love the blueberry dessert
Best coffee spot in town! So happy to have them in Waxhaw! They thought of everything...  Options for non-coffee/tea drinkers, dairy free options, even kids tables outside!

reviews_data.review_text: Great quality coffee in Waxhaw!!
So excited to have them in Waxhaw! I’ve been to their Lancaster location which was wonderful.
Love this place, so thankful to have them in the neighborhood 🙌
Nice place in waxhaw. A lot of outdoor seating.
